==Input impedance of transmission line==
The characteristic impedance formula_76 of a transmission line is the ratio of the amplitude of a &quot;single&quot; voltage wave to its current wave. Since most transmission lines also have a reflected wave, the characteristic impedance is generally not the impedance that is measured on the line.

The impedance measured at a given distance formula_77 from the load impedance formula_78 may be expressed as

:formula_79,

where formula_30 is the propagation constant and formula_81 is the voltage reflection coefficient measured at the load end of the transmission line. Alternatively, the above formula can be rearranged to express the input impedance in terms of the load impedance rather than the load voltage reflection coefficient:

:formula_82.

